_comment: This file is loaded instead of config.json when analyzing an LKM. The analysis of LKMs requires a different set of options compared to the analysis of user-space programs.

CWE134._comment: Functions that take format string arguments.

CWE252._comment: All exported functions annotated with warn_unused_result.

CWE416._comment: Functions that invalidate the pointer passed as the first argument.

CWE467._comment: Any function that takes something of type `size_t` could be a possible candidate.

CWE476._comment: Any function that either returns a pointer to a valid object, or a value that indicates an error.
Every function in the Linux LKM API that returns a pointer to a non-pointer type.

CWE789._comment: Allocation functions that accept a size argument.
